A MAN has been arrested in connection with a robbery at a Glasgow hairdressers. Police helicopter sent to Shettleston after incident A MAN has been arrested in connection with a robbery at a Glasgow hairdressers.Officers were called out the Shettleston area at around 10.30am on Friday.Police Scotland's helicopter was deployed to Wellshot Road as officers carried out a search of the area.A 44-year-old man was arrested shortly after the alleged incident.He is expected to appear at Glasgow Sheriff Court on Monday. 